        "title": "Android: Override a method in higher API level",
        "body": "<p>How can I override a method which is present only in a higher API level than my minimum level?<\/p>\n\n<p>Specifically I want to override a class which extends <em>View<\/em> class and I need to override <em>setBackground()<\/em> method.<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>but when I <strong>use<\/strong> <em>\"@Override\"<\/em> Annotation I get the error:<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>\"error: method does not override or implement a method from a supertype\"<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>and when I <strong>don't use<\/strong> the <em>\"@Override\"<\/em> Annotation I get the error:<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>\"This method is not overriding anything with the current build target, but will in API level 16 (current target is 10)\"<\/p>\n",
